defaultHowever, 
defaultwe 
defaultabsolutely must avoid moving care out of hospitals without 
defaultfirst establishing
default a clear plan for how services in the community 
defaultshould
default to be organised and resourced to accommodate this
default change
default. In RCGP's view we need to effect change in three key areas:
default&#xa0;
default(defaultidefault) Service redesign, defaultcare planningdefault and ‘communities defaultofdefault practice’default&#xa0;
defaultWe need to establish new models of generalist-led care in the community in order to meet the changing needs of patients with long term conditions. Currently 
defaultit is s
defaultt
defaultill the norm
default that different professionals work within their own organisational silos, funding systems and cultures. We need to redesign services in a way that encourages shared ownership and responsibility for ensuring that those with long term conditions are supported to manage and plan their own care.
default&#xa0;
defaultOn
defaulte potential model is to create multi-disciplinary teams
default 
defaultbased with
defaultin primary care
default.
default This consists of different health care professionals, drawn from the wider primary care team, working together to deliver routine care, health advice and case management to high-risk patients. The model ensures such patients have access to longer appointment times, and health professionals are trained in skills such as chronic dise
defaultase management, shared decision
default making and prevention. 
default&#xa0;
defaultAnother
default powerful 
defaulttool
default is care planning
default, an approach pioneered by the diabetes ‘Year of Care’ initiative (se
defaulte section 5 below)
default. This involves agreeing
default a plan to improve an individual’s health and well-being, and co-ordinating across a range of health, social care and other professionals to ensure the provision of support and services to address the patient’s needs.
default 
defaultThere is strong evidence that care planning c
defaulta
defaultn improve outcomes for patients, reduced 
defaultunnecessary
default hospital admissions and save money
default.
default 
defaultWe
default now need
default to
default embed care planning into the 'core business' of general practice and other parts of the system.
default 
defaultRCGP 
defaultis hosting
default a consortium of charities and primary care organisations 
defaultto develop 
defaulta set of 'communities 
defaultof
default practice'
